content:
Supervisors can monitor agents and their work in the Agents tab of Omni-Channel Supervisor. By default, supervisors can view all online agents. Supervisors can also view offline agents, if they have read access on the Service Resource object.

To change the user profile permissions for the Service Resource object: Customize Application

An offline agent is a user with a Service Resource that is set as Active and has a Resource Type of Agent.

To permit particular supervisors to view offline agents, set the access at the user profile level. 

Supervisors who have visibility on more than 1,000 agents with associated service resources sometimes see inconsistent numbers of offline agents.

Setting the access at the user profile level shows all offline agents to supervisors with the profile. To reduce the set of agents shown to the agents that they oversee, create a supervisor configuration.

title: Showing Offline Agents in Omni Supervisor
